def hist_box_plot(feature: str, df, color='green', figsize=(12, 6), bins='auto', kde=False,
             fontsize=12, hue=None, multiple='layer') -> None:
    try:
        fig, ax = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=figsize)
        sns.histplot(data=df,
                     x=feature,
                     color=color,
                     bins=bins,
                     kde=kde,
                     hue=hue,
                     multiple=multiple,
                     ax=ax[0])
        ax[0].set_xlabel(f'{feature}', fontsize=fontsize)
        ax[0].set_ylabel(f' ', fontsize=12);
        ax[0].set_title(f'  {feature}', fontsize=15)
        ax[0].grid()
        
        sns.boxplot(data=df,
                   x=feature,
                   ax=ax[1])
        ax[1].set_xlabel(f'{feature}')
        ax[1].set_title(f'  {feature}', fontsize=15)
        ax[1].grid()
        plt.show()
    except Exception:
        print('-      hist_plot...\n    ')
        
def pie_plot(feature, df, figsize=(12, 6), fontsize=12):
    try:
        plt.figure(figsize=figsize)
        fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=figsize);
        alpha = df[feature].value_counts()
        ax.pie(alpha.values, labels=alpha.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
        ax.set_xlabel(f"  {feature}", fontsize=fontsize)
        plt.show();
    except Exception:
        print('-      hist_plot...\n    ')
        
def hist_plot(feature: str, df, color='green', figsize=(12, 6), bins='auto', kde=False,
             fontsize=12, hue=None, multiple='layer') -> None:
    try:
        fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=figsize)
        sns.histplot(data=df,
                     x=feature,
                     color=color,
                     bins=bins,
                     kde=kde,
                     hue=hue,
                     multiple=multiple,
                     ax=ax)
        ax.set_xlabel(f' {feature}', fontsize=fontsize)
        ax.set_ylabel(f' ', fontsize=12);
        ax.set_title(f'  {feature}', fontsize=15)
        plt.show()
    except Exception:
        print('-      hist_plot...\n    ')
        
def count_plot(feature: str, df, color='green', figsize=(12, 6),
             fontsize=12, hue=None) -> None:
    try:
        fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=figsize)
        sns.countplot(data=df,
                     x=feature,
                     color=color,
                     hue=hue,
                     ax=ax)
        ax.set_xlabel(f' {feature}', fontsize=fontsize)
        ax.set_ylabel(f' ', fontsize=12);
        ax.set_title(f'  {feature}', fontsize=15)
        plt.show()
    except Exception:
        print('-      count_plot...\n    ')
        
        
def kde_plot(x, hue, train_quit):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(15, 12))
    sns.kdeplot(x='salary',
                data=train_quit,
                ax=ax[0]
                )
    ax[0].set_xlabel(f' {x}')
    ax[0].set_ylabel(f' {x}')
    ax[0].set_title(f' {x}')
    ax[0].grid()
    
    sns.kdeplot(x='salary',
                data=train_quit,
                hue=hue,
                ax=ax[1]
                )
    ax[1].set_xlabel(f' {x}')
    ax[1].set_ylabel(f' {x}')
    ax[1].grid()
    ax[1].set_title(f' {x}    {hue}');

SMAPE:

In [60]:
def smape(y_true, y_pred):
    """
          (SMAPE).
    
    Args:
        y_true: array-like. True values.
        y_pred: array-like. Predicted values.
    
    Return:
        smape_value: float. SMAPE value.
    """
    y_true = np.array(y_true)
    y_pred = np.array(y_pred)
    
    denominator = (np.abs(y_true) + np.abs(y_pred)) / 2
    difference = np.abs(y_true - y_pred) / denominator
    
    return np.mean(difference) * 100

smape_scorer = make_scorer(smape, greater_is_better=False)
